+  "response": "The `npm run build` command failed again with the same TypeScript errors related to template literals and the `++` operator. This indicates the previous corrections, while syntactically sound in isolation, were not correctly applied or interpreted by the build process. The persistent errors suggest a subtle issue with how these constructs are being parsed in the project's environment.\n\nI will apply a refined approach to address the template literal and increment operator issues. The key is to ensure that template literals are correctly formed and that any variable increment operations are handled distinctly from string construction.\n\n**Revised Files:**\n\n**`src/cart/index.ts`**\n```typescript\nimport { EventBus, CartService, CartUpdatedEvent, OrderItem, Events } from '../types';\n\ninterface Cart {\n  id: string;\n  userId: string;\n  items: Map<string, { productId: string; quantity: number }>; // Map productId to item details\n}\n\nexport function createCartService(bus: EventBus): CartService {\n  const carts = new Map<string, Cart>();\n  let nextCartId = 1;\n\n  const generateCartId = (): string => {\n    const id = `cart_${nextCartId}`;\n    nextCartId++; // Increment after capturing the value for the ID\n    return id;\n  };\n\n  const getCart = (cartId: string): Cart | null => {\n    const cart = carts.get(cartId);\n    return cart || null;\n  };\n\n  const createCart = (userId: string): string => {\n    const id = generateCartId();\n    const newCart: Cart = { id, userId, items: new Map<string, { productId: string; quantity: number }>() };\n    carts.set(id, newCart);\n    return id;\n  };\n\n  const addItem = (cartId: string, productId: string, quantity: number): void => {\n    if (quantity <= 0) return; // Ignore invalid quantities\n\n    const cart = getCart(cartId);\n    if (!cart) return; // Cart not found\n\n    const existingItem = cart.items.get(productId);\n    if (existingItem) {\n      existingItem.quantity += quantity;\n    } else {\n      cart.items.set(productId, { productId, quantity });\n    }\n    emitCartUpdate(cartId);\n  };\n\n  const removeItem = (cartId: string, productId: string): void => {\n    const cart = getCart(cartId);\n    if (!cart) return;\n\n    if (cart.items.has(productId)) {\n      cart.items.delete(productId);\n      emitCartUpdate(cartId);\n    }\n  };\n\n  const clearCart = (cartId: string): void => {\n    const cart = getCart(cartId);\n    if (!cart) return;\n\n    cart.items.clear();\n    emitCartUpdate(cartId);\n  };\n\n  const updateQuantity = (cartId: string, productId: string, quantity: number): void => {\n    const cart = getCart(cartId);\n    if (!cart) return;\n\n    if (quantity <= 0) {\n      // If quantity is zero or less, remove the item\n      cart.items.delete(productId);\n    } else {\n      const item = cart.items.get(productId);\n      if (item) {\n        item.quantity = quantity;\n      } else {\n        // If item doesn't exist and quantity is positive, add it\n        cart.items.set(productId, { productId, quantity });\n      }\n    }\n    emitCartUpdate(cartId);\n  };\n\n  const emitCartUpdate = (cartId: string) => {\n    const cart = getCart(cartId);\n    if (!cart) return;\n\n    const formattedItems = Array.from(cart.items.values());\n    const eventPayload: CartUpdatedEvent = {\n      cartId: cart.id,\n      userId: cart.userId,\n      items: formattedItems,\n    };\n    bus.emit(Events.CART_UPDATED, eventPayload);\n  };\n\n  return {\n    createCart,\n    addItem,\n    removeItem,\n    getCart,\n    clearCart,\n    updateQuantity,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**`src/catalog/index.ts`**\n```typescript\nimport { EventBus, Product, ProductCreatedEvent, ProductService, Events } from '../types';\n\ninterface Product {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  price: number;\n  category: string;\n}\n\nexport function createCatalogService(bus: EventBus): ProductService {\n  const products = new Map<string, Product>();\n  let nextProductId = 1;\n\n  const generateProductId = (): string => {\n    const id = `prod_${nextProductId}`;\n    nextProductId++;\n    return id;\n  };\n\n  const getProduct = (id: string): Product | null => {\n    const product = products.get(id);\n    return product || null; // Return null if not found, as per interface\n  };\n\n  const listProducts = (category?: string): Product[] => {\n    if (category) {\n      return Array.from(products.values()).filter(p => p.category === category);\n    }\n    return Array.from(products.values());\n  };\n\n  const searchProducts = (query: string): Product[] => {\n    const lowerCaseQuery = query.toLowerCase();\n    return Array.from(products.values()).filter(p =>\n      p.name.toLowerCase().includes(lowerCaseQuery) ||\n      p.id.toLowerCase().includes(lowerCaseQuery)\n    );\n  };\n\n  const createProduct = (name: string, price: number, category: string): string => {\n    const id = generateProductId();\n    const newProduct: Product = { id, name, price, category };\n    products.set(id, newProduct);\n    const eventPayload: ProductCreatedEvent = { productId: newProduct.id, name: newProduct.name, price: newProduct.price, category: newProduct.category };\n    bus.emit(Events.PRODUCT_CREATED, eventPayload);\n    return newProduct.id; // Return productId as per interface\n  };\n\n  const updateProduct = (productId: string, updates: Partial<{ name: string; price: number; category: string }>): void => {\n    const existingProduct = products.get(productId);\n    if (!existingProduct) {\n      return;\n    }\n    const updatedProduct: Product = { ...existingProduct, ...updates };\n    products.set(productId, updatedProduct);\n  };\n\n  const removeProduct = (productId: string): boolean => {\n    return products.delete(productId);\n  };\n\n  return {\n    getProduct,\n    listProducts,\n    searchProducts,\n    createProduct,\n    updateProduct,\n    removeProduct,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**`src/notifications/index.ts`**\nEnsured template literals are correctly formed with backticks.\n```typescript\nimport { EventBus, NotificationService, NotificationSentEvent, OrderStatusChangedEvent, PaymentProcessedEvent, Events } from '../types';\n\ninterface UserNotification {\n  type: string;\n  message: string;\n  timestamp: number;\n}\n\nexport function createNotificationsService(bus: EventBus): NotificationService {\n  const userNotifications = new Map<string, UserNotification[]>();\n  const orderUserMap = new Map<string, string>();\n\n  const sendNotification = (userId: string, type: string, message: string) => {\n    const notification: UserNotification = { type, message, timestamp: Date.now() };\n    const notifications = userNotifications.get(userId) || [];\n    notifications.push(notification);\n    userNotifications.set(userId, notifications);\n\n    const eventPayload: NotificationSentEvent = { userId, type, message };\n    bus.emit(Events.NOTIFICATION_SENT, eventPayload);\n  };\n\n  const handleOrderCreated = (event: { orderId: string; userId: string }) => {\n    orderUserMap.set(event.orderId, event.userId);\n  };\n  bus.on(Events.ORDER_CREATED, handleOrderCreated);\n\n  const handleOrderStatusChanged = (event: OrderStatusChangedEvent) => {\n    const userId = orderUserMap.get(event.orderId);\n    if (userId) {\n      sendNotification(\n        userId,\n        `order:${event.status}`, // e.g., \"order:shipped\"\n        `Order ${event.orderId} status changed from ${event.previousStatus} to ${event.status}.`\n      );\n    } else {\n      console.warn(`User ID not found for order ${event.orderId} when handling status change.`);\n    }\n  };\n  bus.on(Events.ORDER_STATUS_CHANGED, handleOrderStatusChanged);\n\n  const handlePaymentProcessed = (event: PaymentProcessedEvent) => {\n    const userId = orderUserMap.get(event.orderId);\n    if (userId) {\n      if (event.status === 'success') {\n        sendNotification(userId, 'payment:success', `Payment for order ${event.orderId} was successful.`);\n      } else if (event.status === 'failed') {\n        sendNotification(userId, 'payment:failed', `Payment for order ${event.orderId} failed: ${event.error || 'Unknown error'}.`);\n      } else if (event.status === 'timeout') {\n        sendNotification(userId, 'payment:timeout', `Payment for order ${event.orderId} timed out.`);\n      }\n    } else {\n      console.warn(`User ID not found for order ${event.orderId} when handling payment processed.`);\n    }\n  };\n  bus.on(Events.PAYMENT_PROCESSED, handlePaymentProcessed);\n\n  const subscribe = (userId: string): void => {\n    if (!userNotifications.has(userId)) {\n      userNotifications.set(userId, []);\n    }\n  };\n\n  const getNotifications = (userId: string): UserNotification[] => {\n    return userNotifications.get(userId) || [];\n  };\n\n  return {\n    subscribe,\n    getNotifications,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**`src/orders/index.ts`**\n```typescript\nimport { EventBus, OrderService, Order, OrderStatus, OrderCreatedEvent, OrderStatusChangedEvent, Events } from '../types';\n\ninterface OrderInternal extends Omit<Order, 'status'> {\n  status: OrderStatus;\n  previousStatus?: OrderStatus; // Track previous status for events\n}\n\nexport function createOrdersService(bus: EventBus): OrderService {\n  const orders = new Map<string, OrderInternal>();\n  let nextOrderId = 1;\n\n  const generateOrderId = (): string => {\n    const id = `order_${nextOrderId}`;\n    nextOrderId++;\n    return id;\n  };\n\n  const getOrder = (orderId: string): Order | null => {\n    const order = orders.get(orderId);\n    if (!order) return null;\n    const { previousStatus, ...rest } = order;\n    return rest;\n  };\n\n  const createOrder = (userId: string, cartId: string, total: number): string => {\n    const id = generateOrderId();\n    const newOrder: OrderInternal = {\n      id,\n      userId,\n      cartId, // Store cartId for reference\n      total,\n      status: OrderStatus.PENDING,\n      previousStatus: undefined,\n    };\n    orders.set(id, newOrder);\n\n    const eventPayload: OrderCreatedEvent = {\n      orderId: newOrder.id,\n      userId: newOrder.userId,\n      cartId: newOrder.cartId,\n      total: newOrder.total,\n    };\n    bus.emit(Events.ORDER_CREATED, eventPayload);\n\n    return id;\n  };\n\n  const updateStatus = (orderId: string, status: OrderStatus): void => {\n    const order = orders.get(orderId);\n    if (!order) {\n      console.warn(`Order not found for status update: ${orderId}`);\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (order.status === status) {\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const previousStatus = order.status;\n    order.previousStatus = previousStatus;\n    order.status = status;\n\n    const eventPayload: OrderStatusChangedEvent = {\n      orderId: order.id,\n      status: order.status,\n      previousStatus: order.previousStatus,\n    };\n    bus.emit(Events.ORDER_STATUS_CHANGED, eventPayload);\n  };\n\n  const listOrders = (userId: string): Order[] => {\n    const userOrders = Array.from(orders.values())\n      .filter(order => order.userId === userId)\n      .map(order => {\n        const { previousStatus, ...rest } = order;\n        return rest;\n      });\n    return userOrders;\n  };\n\n  return {\n    createOrder,\n    getOrder,\n    updateStatus,\n    listOrders,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**`src/payment/index.ts`**\n```typescript\nimport { EventBus, PaymentService, PaymentProcessedEvent, Events } from '../types';\n\ninterface PaymentOptions {\n  simulateSuccess?: boolean;\n  simulateFailure?: boolean;\n  simulateTimeout?: boolean;\n  timeoutDuration?: number; // milliseconds\n}\n\nexport function createPaymentService(bus: EventBus, options: PaymentOptions = {}): PaymentService {\n  const {\n    simulateSuccess = true,\n    simulateFailure = false,\n    simulateTimeout = false,\n    timeoutDuration = 2000,\n  } = options;\n\n  let nextTransactionId = 1;\n  const processedTransactions = new Map<string, { orderId: string; amount: number; status: 'success' | 'refunded' }>();\n\n  const generateTransactionId = (): string => {\n    const id = `txn_${nextTransactionId}`;\n    nextTransactionId++;\n    return id;\n  };\n\n  const processPayment = async (orderId: string, amount: number): Promise<{ status: 'success' | 'failed' | 'timeout'; transactionId?: string; error?: string }> => {\n    const transactionId = generateTransactionId();\n\n    if (simulateTimeout) {\n      await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, timeoutDuration));\n    }\n\n    let result: { status: 'success' | 'failed' | 'timeout'; transactionId?: string; error?: string };\n\n    if (simulateFailure) {\n      result = { status: 'failed', transactionId, error: 'Simulated payment failure' };\n    } else if (simulateSuccess || (!simulateFailure && !simulateTimeout)) {\n      result = { status: 'success', transactionId };\n      processedTransactions.set(transactionId, { orderId, amount, status: 'success' });\n    } else {\n      result = { status: 'timeout', transactionId, error: 'Simulated payment timeout' };\n    }\n\n    const eventPayload: PaymentProcessedEvent = {\n      orderId: orderId,\n      status: result.status === 'success' ? 'success' : result.status === 'failed' ? 'failed' : 'timeout',\n      transactionId: result.transactionId,\n      error: result.error,\n    };\n    bus.emit(Events.PAYMENT_PROCESSED, eventPayload);\n\n    return result;\n  };\n\n  const refund = async (transactionId: string): Promise<boolean> => {\n    const transaction = processedTransactions.get(transactionId);\n\n    if (!transaction || transaction.status !== 'success') {\n      console.warn(`Cannot refund: Transaction ${transactionId} not found or already refunded/failed.`);\n      return false;\n    }\n\n    transaction.status = 'refunded';\n    processedTransactions.set(transactionId, transaction);\n    console.log(`Refund processed for transaction ${transactionId}`);\n    return true;\n  };\n\n  return {\n    processPayment,\n    refund,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**`src/pricing/index.ts`**\nEnsured template literal syntax is correct.\n```typescript\nimport { EventBus, PricingService, OrderItem, Events, PriceCalculatedEvent } from '../types';\n\ninterface DiscountCode {\n  code: string;\n  percentage: number; // e.g., 0.10 for 10%\n}\n\nexport function createPricingService(bus: EventBus): PricingService {\n  const TAX_RATE = 0.10; // 10%\n  const discountCodes = new Map<string, DiscountCode>();\n  const productPrices = new Map<string, number>();\n\n  const handleProductCreated = (event: { productId: string; price: number }) => {\n    productPrices.set(event.productId, event.price);\n  };\n  bus.on(Events.PRODUCT_CREATED, handleProductCreated);\n\n  const addDiscountCode = (code: string, percentage: number): void => {\n    if (percentage < 0 || percentage > 1) {\n      console.warn(`Invalid discount percentage: ${percentage}. Must be between 0 and 1.`);\n      return;\n    }\n    discountCodes.set(code, { code, percentage });\n  };\n\n  const getPrice = (productId: string): number => {\n    const price = productPrices.get(productId);\n    if (price === undefined) {\n      console.warn(`Price not found for product: ${productId}`);\n      return 0; // Default to 0 if price is not set\n    }\n    return price;\n  };\n\n  const calculateTotal = (\n    items: Array<{ productId: string; quantity: number }>,\n    discountCode?: string\n  ): { subtotal: number; discount: number; tax: number; total: number } => {\n    let subtotal = 0;\n\n    for (const item of items) {\n      const price = getPrice(item.productId);\n      if (price === 0 && !productPrices.has(item.productId)) {\n        console.warn(`Unknown product encountered: ${item.productId}`);\n        continue; // Skip this item\n      }\n      subtotal += price * item.quantity;\n    }\n\n    let discountAmount = 0;\n    let discountPercentage = 0;\n    if (discountCode) {\n      const discount = discountCodes.get(discountCode);\n      if (discount) {\n        discountPercentage = discount.percentage;\n        discountAmount = subtotal * discountPercentage;\n        subtotal -= discountAmount; // Reduce subtotal by discount amount\n      } else {\n        console.warn(`Discount code not found: ${discountCode}`);\n      }\n    }\n\n    const taxAmount = subtotal * TAX_RATE;\n    const total = subtotal + taxAmount;\n\n    const eventPayload: PriceCalculatedEvent = {\n      cartId: 'N/A', // This service doesn't manage cart IDs directly\n      subtotal: subtotal + discountAmount, // Original subtotal before discount\n      discount: discountAmount,\n      tax: taxAmount,\n      total: total,\n    };\n    bus.emit(Events.PRICE_CALCULATED, eventPayload);\n\n    return {\n      subtotal: subtotal + discountAmount, // Return original subtotal before discount\n      discount: discountAmount,\n      tax: taxAmount,\n      total: total,\n    };\n  };\n\n  return {\n    addDiscountCode,\n    getPrice,\n    calculateTotal,\n  };\n}\n```\nI have rewritten the ID generation functions in `src/cart`, `src/catalog`, `src/orders`, and `src/payment` to ensure that the template literal `\\`prefix_\\${variable}\\`` is used, and the increment operation `variable++` is performed on a separate line. I have also re-verified the template literal syntax in `src/notifications` and `src/pricing` for any potential subtle errors. I will now run `npm run build` again.",
